The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Simplex lines up overseas expansion 

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Simplex director Amitabh Mundhra (right) and chairman and managing director B. D. Mundhra in Calcutta on Tuesday. Picture by Kishor Roy Chowdhury

 Calcutta, Feb. 1: Simplex Concrete Piles (India) Limited will set up special purpose vehicles (SPV) in Dubai, Yemen, Russia, Singapore and Kuwait.

 ?We plan to increase our exposure in the overseas markets. In the next five years, we hope revenues from these markets to contribute 50 per cent of our total turnover,? director Amitabh Mundhra said.

 The company already has a SPV in Bahrain and is currently bidding for projects in other overseas markets.

 ?We expect to participate in the project of Dubai metro. Our credentials as participants in Delhi metro should help,? Mundhra said.

 The company is actively bidding for projects in the countries where it plans to set up the SPVs. ?Till now, we have received contract worth $20-30 million in Russia. However, we hope to get bigger contracts in the near future,? added Mundhra. 

 The SPV at Moscow in Russia will be set up in a month, while that in Singapore within 2-3 months, added Mundhra.

 In the current financial year, revenue from the overseas projects is expected to contribute 12 per cent of the total turnover of the company, said Mundhra.

 ?We expect to close the year with a turnover of Rs 900 crore against Rs 640 crore in the previous fiscal,? chairman and managing director B. D. Mundhra said.

 For the third quarter ended December 31, the infrastructure solutions provider registered an jump of 343.5 per cent in its net profit at Rs 9.73 crore compared with Rs 2.23 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal.

 The profit before tax of the company rose by 257.06 per cent to Rs 11.39 crore from Rs 3.26 crore in the same period last year. The net sales registered an increase of 71.5 per cent to Rs 261.35 crore from Rs 152.39 crore during the last fiscal period. 




